abstract: The City of New York may contract with Google to digitize 90,000 vintage photos of Manhattan buildings. The city wants to sell copies of the images, and Google wants to use them in its Maps program.
snippet: The City of New York may contract with Google to digitize 90,000 vintage photos of Manhattan buildings. The city wants to sell copies of the images, and Google wants to use them in its Maps program.
lead_paragraph: If Google can help legions of companies sell their products, why not help New York City sell some vintage photos?

headline.main: Vintage New York Photos Might End Up on Google

abstract: Gowalla, a new mobile social network that doubles as a virtual scavenger hunt, has uncovered $8.4 million in venture funding.
snippet: Gowalla, a new mobile social network that doubles as a virtual scavenger hunt, has uncovered $8.4 million in venture funding.
lead_paragraph: When it comes to location-based social networking, there are plenty of upstarts vying for real estate on your mobile phone’s screen: Foursquare, Loopt, BrightKite, GyPSii and Gowalla, to name a few.

headline.main: A Scavenger-Hunt Social Network Finds Funding

abstract: AOL began trading as its own public company on Wednesday, after its long planned spin-off from Time Warner was finally made official.
snippet: AOL began trading as its own public company on Wednesday, after its long planned spin-off from Time Warner was finally made official.
lead_paragraph: The long, chaotic and star-crossed relationship between AOL and Time Warner has finally ended in divorce, The New York Times’s Tim Arango reports.

headline.main: AOL Quietly Returns to Life on Its Own
